{"title_page": "Desh Subba", "text_new": "{{Notability|Biographies|date=December 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox philosopher\n| region = \n| era = \n| name = Desh Subba\n| birth_name = Desh Bahadur Limbu\n| birth_date  = {{birth date|1965|12|06|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Dharan, Nepal|Dharan]], [[Nepal]]\n| alma_mater = \n| thesis_title = \n| thesis_url = \n| thesis_year = \n| school_tradition = \n| main_interests = \n| notable_ideas =\n| influences = \n| influenced =\n| spouse = \n}}\n\n'''Desh Subba''' is a [[Nepal]]-born [[author]] and poet.\n\nHis book ''[[Philosophy of Fearism]]'' published through [[Xlibris]], USA. It portrays fear as major part of life. According to him life is conducted, guided and controlled by fear. He also argue utility of fear, impact of fear, dephilosophy of philosophy etc.\n\nBorn in [[Dharan, Nepal|Dharan]], [[Eastern Development Region, Nepal|Eastern Nepal]], Subba lives with his family in [[Hong Kong]].\n\nFathers' Name: Kubir Jung Limbu Mother's Name: Tilmati Limbu Education: Master in business administration Writing field: Philosophy of Fearism Published Novel Books: Four novels, Doshi Karm 2050 B.S, Apman 2052 B.S., Sahid 2056 B.S., Aadibashi 2064 B.S.\n\nHe started fearism as a literary movement in 1999 with fiction and in 2011 with line poetry. He's published four novels in Nepali. His third novel, ''Aadibashi'', is recently published in English, titled ''Journey to Fearless''. In this novel he experiments with fearism in literature. He has received four book awards in 2015: International Nepali Literature Society's (Washington, DC) Dr. Shyam Karki/Indira Karki Diaspora Best Analytical Book of the Year Award 2014-15 for Bhayabad (Philosophy of Fearism), National Indie Excellence Awards (winner), International Book Awards (finalist) and New York Book Festival Award (honorable mention) and 2015 Southern California Book Festival Awards (honorable mention). He continues to write while speaking at universities, like Hong Kong University and elsewhere about fearism. He is the leading fearism spokesperson in the East, and co-founder of the Fearism Study Center (2009-) in Dharan, Nepal.\n\nInvolved in organization: Hong Kong Nepalese Literary Academy.\n\n==Awards==\n* Winner, National Indie Excellence Award, 2015\n* Finalist, International Book Award, 2015\n* Honorable Mention, Southern California Book Festival, 2015\n* Winner, Dr. Shyam Karki and Indira Karki Award, 2015\n* Honorable Mention, New York Book Festival Award, 2015\n* Award from Dhaka University, 2016\n\n==Bibliography==\n* ''Philosophy of Fearism'' (2014)<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/philosophy-of-fearism-desh-subba/1119974379 | title = Philosophy of Fearism: Life Is Conducted, Directed and Controlled by the Fear. | publisher = Barnes & Noble | author = Desh Subba | accessdate = 21 December 2015}}</ref>\n* ''Philosophy of Fearism: a First East-West dialogue'' with Michael Fisher (2016)\n* ''Tribesmen's Journey to Fearless''\n* ''Fear, Law and Criminology Critical Issues in applying the Philosophy of Fearism'' with Michael Fisher and Maria Kumar\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/books/article/1746210/fear-driver-human-progress-hong-kong-author-argues|title=Fear is the driver of human progress, Hong Kong author argues|date=25 March 2015|work=[[South China Morning Post]]|access-date=21 December 2015}}\n* http://www.themileage.org/2015/02/philosophy-of-fearism.html {{unreliable source?|date=December 2015}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.internationalbookawards.com/2015awardannouncement.html|title=International Book Awards - Honoring Excellence in Independent & Mainstream Publishing|publisher=internationalbookawards.com|access-date=21 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151229054615/http://internationalbookawards.com/2015awardannouncement.html|archive-date=29 December 2015|url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.indieexcellen